This paper deals with the task of extracting news events from Twitter, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also involves machine learning and data mining techniques, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with the challenge of dealing with noisy and unstructured data, which falls under the sub-category cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the paper involves the task of identifying relevant information from a large volume of data, which is covered in sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
